# Sentinel — Complete Architectural Overview

## 1. What Is Sentinel

Sentinel is an **AI-powered observability platform with a prompt firewall**. It ingests production error logs, sanitizes sensitive data (emails, IPs, API keys, tokens, passwords) using regex + database-driven knowledge policies, then uses Google Gemini AI to analyze the root cause and suggest resolutions — all without leaking sensitive data to the LLM.

---

## 2. System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client Integration"
        SDK["@sentinel/sdk (npm package)"]
        SENTRY["or Sentry-like webhook"]
        CURL["or direct HTTP"]
    end

    subgraph "API Gateway :3000"
        GW["Express + CORS"]
        AUTH["JWT Auth Middleware"]
        CACHE["Redis Cache"]
        RL["Rate Limiter (Redis)"]
    end

    subgraph "Microservices"
        US["User Service :4000"]
        FS["Firewall Service :4002"]
        IS["Incident Service :4001"]
        AS["Audit Service :4003"]
        NS["Notification Service :4004"]
    end

    subgraph "AI"
        GEMINI["Gemini 2.5 Flash"]
    end

    subgraph "Infrastructure"
        KAFKA["Kafka + Zookeeper"]
        PG["PostgreSQL (shared)"]
        REDIS["Redis"]
    end

    SDK --> GW
    SENTRY --> GW
    CURL --> GW
    GW --> AUTH --> RL --> CACHE
    GW -->|"proxy /users"| US
    GW -->|"proxy /firewall"| FS
    GW -->|"proxy /incidents"| IS

    FS -->|"produce events"| KAFKA
    IS -->|"consume + produce"| KAFKA
    AS -->|"consume"| KAFKA
    NS -->|"consume"| KAFKA

    FS -->|"direct call"| GEMINI

    US --> PG
    IS --> PG
    FS --> PG
    AS --> PG
    NS --> PG

    GW --> REDIS
    IS --> REDIS
```

