## 3. Complete Event Flow (with traceId)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant FW as Firewall :4002
    participant K as Kafka
    participant IS as Incident :4001
    participant AI as Gemini AI
    participant AS as Audit :4003
    participant NS as Notification :4004

    C->>GW: POST /firewall/api/ingest {logs}
    GW->>FW: proxy → POST /api/ingest

    Note over FW: Generate traceId + tempId
    FW->>FW: sanitizeLogs(db, log, userId, traceId)
    Note over FW: Regex: emails, IPs, keys, passwords, tokens
    Note over FW: DB policies: blocked keywords, allowed domains
    FW-->>FW: Write system_events (with traceId in payload)

    FW->>K: produce "incident.created" {tempId, traceId, sanitizedSnippet}
    FW-->>K: produce "policy.violation" {tempId, traceId, violations[]}

    K->>IS: consume "incident.created"
    IS->>IS: Deduplicate by tempId
    IS->>IS: Store incident (incidentId = new UUID)
    IS->>IS: Backfill system_events (mark processed where traceId matches)
    IS->>K: produce "incident.stored" {incidentId, traceId, sanitizedSnippet}

    K->>FW: consume "incident.stored"
    FW->>AI: analyzeIncident(sanitizedSnippet) — direct function call
    Note over AI: Returns {summary, root_cause, resolution, confidence}
    FW->>K: produce "incident.analyzed" {incidentId, traceId, summary, root_cause, resolution, confidence}

    K->>IS: consume "incident.analyzed"
    IS->>IS: UPDATE incidents SET ai_summary = {...}
    IS->>K: produce "audit.event" {entity_id, traceId, action, details}
    IS-->>K: produce "alert.created" (only if confidence > 0.7 AND severity high/critical)

    K->>AS: consume "audit.event" → INSERT audit_logs
    K->>AS: consume "alert.created" → INSERT alerts
    K->>AS: consume "policy.violation" → INSERT policy_logs (per violation)

    K->>NS: consume "alert.created"
    NS->>NS: INSERT system_events
    NS->>NS: Send Slack webhook
    NS->>NS: Send Email via Resend
    NS->>NS: Mark system_event processed
```

---

## 4. Service-by-Service Breakdown

### 4.1 API Gateway (:3000)
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Single entry point, auth, rate limiting, caching, request proxying |
| **Routes** | `/users/*` → User Service, `/incidents/*` → Incident Service, `/firewall/*` → Firewall Service |
| **Middleware** | JWT auth (`@shared/utils`), Redis rate limiter, Redis cache with `X-Cache` headers |
| **Headers** | Strips `host` and `content-length` before forwarding |

### 4.2 User Service (:4000)
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Role** | User registration, login, CRUD |
| **Auth** | bcrypt password hashing, JWT token generation |
| **Endpoints** | `POST /register`, `POST /login`, `GET /`, `GET /:id`, `PATCH /:id`, `DELETE /:id` |
| **Health** | `GET /health` |

### 4.3 Firewall Service (:4002)
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Log ingestion, sanitization, AI analysis |
| **HTTP** | `POST /api/ingest` (ingestion), `POST /api/analyze` (direct AI test) |
| **Kafka Producer** | `incident.created`, `policy.violation` |
| **Kafka Consumer** | `incident.stored` → calls Gemini → produces `incident.analyzed` |
| **Sanitization** | 5 regex patterns + DB knowledge policies |

### 4.4 Incident Service (:4001)
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Incident storage, CRUD, AI result updates |
| **HTTP** | Full CRUD on `/incidents` (auth-protected) |
| **Kafka Consumer 1** | `incident.created` → store + produce `incident.stored` |
| **Kafka Consumer 2** | `incident.analyzed` → update `ai_summary` + produce `audit.event` + conditionally `alert.created` |
| **Features** | Pagination, filtering, search, duplicate detection via `tempId` |

### 4.5 Audit Service (:4003)
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Role** | Compliance and audit trail |
| **Kafka Consumer** | `audit.event` → `audit_logs`, `alert.created` → `alerts`, `policy.violation` → `policy_logs` |
| **Health** | `GET /health` |

### 4.6 Notification Service (:4004)
| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| **Role** | External notifications |
| **Kafka Consumer** | `alert.created` → Slack webhook + Email via Resend |
| **Health** | `GET /health` |

---

## 5. Kafka Topic Registry

| Topic | Producer | Consumer(s) | traceId | Payload |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `incident.created` | Firewall | Incident | ✅ | tempId, traceId, source, severity, sanitizedSnippet |
| `incident.stored` | Incident | Firewall AI | ✅ | incidentId, tempId, traceId, sanitizedSnippet |
| `incident.analyzed` | Firewall AI | Incident | ✅ | incidentId, traceId, summary, root_cause, resolution, confidence |
| `incident.manual_created` | Incident REST | — | ❌ | Raw Incident object (from CRUD API) |
| `audit.event` | Incident | Audit | ✅ | entity_type, entity_id, traceId, action, details |
| `alert.created` | Incident | Audit, Notification | ✅ | incident_id, traceId, severity, message |
| `policy.violation` | Firewall | Audit | ✅ | tempId, traceId, violations[] |

