## 10. Frontend Dashboard Plan

### What the Dashboard Shows

| View | Data Source | API Endpoint (to build) |
|---|---|---|
| **Incident List** | `incidents` table | `GET /incidents` ✅ (already exists, with pagination/filters) |
| **Incident Detail** | `incidents` + `ai_summary` | `GET /incidents/:id` ✅ (already exists) |
| **AI Analysis Card** | `incidents.ai_summary` JSONB | Included in incident detail ✅ |
| **Policy Violations** | `policy_logs` table | `GET /policy-logs` ❌ (needs new endpoint) |
| **Audit Trail** | `audit_logs` table | `GET /audit-logs` ❌ (needs new endpoint) |
| **Alerts Feed** | `alerts` table | `GET /alerts` ❌ (needs new endpoint) |
| **System Events** | `system_events` table | `GET /system-events` ❌ (needs new endpoint) |
| **Knowledge Policies** | `knowledge_policies` table | CRUD `/policies` ❌ (needs new endpoints) |
| **Dashboard Stats** | Aggregated queries | `GET /stats` ❌ (needs new endpoint) |
| **Real-time Updates** | Kafka → WebSocket | WebSocket gateway ❌ (needs new feature) |

### New API Endpoints Needed for Dashboard

```
# Read-only endpoints (add to incident-service or gateway)
GET  /api/stats                     → { totalIncidents, openCount, resolvedCount, avgConfidence }
GET  /api/policy-logs               → paginated policy violation logs
GET  /api/audit-logs                → paginated audit trail
GET  /api/alerts                    → paginated alert feed
GET  /api/alerts/:id/acknowledge    → mark alert as acknowledged

# Knowledge policy management (add to firewall-service)
GET    /api/policies                → list all policies
POST   /api/policies                → create new policy
PATCH  /api/policies/:id            → update policy
DELETE /api/policies/:id            → delete policy

# Real-time (add WebSocket support to gateway)
WS /ws/incidents                    → real-time incident feed
```

### Recommended Frontend Stack

| Choice | Why |
|---|---|
| **Next.js** | SSR for SEO, API routes as BFF, excellent DX |
| **shadcn/ui** | Production-grade components, dark mode built-in |
| **Recharts** | Lightweight charting for stats dashboard |
| **Socket.io** | Real-time incident feed via WebSocket |
| **TanStack Query** | Data fetching with caching and real-time refetch |

### Dashboard Pages

```
/dashboard          → Stats overview, recent incidents, severity distribution chart
/incidents          → Filterable incident list (status, severity, date range)
/incidents/:id      → Incident detail with AI analysis card showing:
                       • Summary, Root Cause, Resolution, Confidence score
                       • Sanitized log snippet
                       • Policy violations triggered
                       • Audit trail timeline
/alerts             → Alert feed with acknowledge buttons
/policies           → Knowledge policy CRUD
/settings           → Team management, notification preferences
```

